🌾 Methodology: Crop Rotation Scheduler
🔹 1. Data Collection
Collect crop-related data such as:
Crop name
Suitable season (Kharif/Rabi/Summer)
Soil type (Loamy, Clay, Sandy)
Nutrient effect (adds or depletes soil nutrients)
Store this data in a file (crops.txt)
🔹 2. Data Storage
Use file handling in C++ to store and retrieve crop data
Each crop record is stored in a structured format:

crop_name season soil nutrient_effect
🔹 3. User Input
The system takes input from the user:
Previous crop grown
Soil type
Current season
🔹 4. Data Processing
Read crop data from file into memory (using arrays/vectors)
Identify the nutrient effect of the previous crop
Filter crops based on:
Matching soil type
Matching season
Avoiding repetition of same crop
🔹 5. Decision Logic
Apply crop rotation rules:
If previous crop depletes nutrients → select crops that add nutrients
If previous crop adds nutrients → select crops that balance or deplete nutrients
🔹 6. Output Generation
Display recommended crops to the user
Provide reason for recommendation (e.g., restores soil fertility)
🔹 7. User Interaction (Menu System)
Provide options:
Add crop data
View crop database
Get recommendation
🔹 8. Validation & Testing
Test with different inputs
Ensure correct recommendations based on rotation rules
Handle cases where no suitable crop is found
